#Approach:

Nth Root of a Number – Hinglish Approach (Binary Search on Answer)

Problem:
Given N aur M, aisa number X find karna hai jiska X^N = M ho.
Agar exact integer root exist karta hai to return X, warna -1 return karo.

Why Binary Search?
Kyuki answer range 1 se M ke beech hi hoga.
Aur hume fast solution chahiye -> O(log M)

Key Idea:
Hum aisa number X find karna chahte hain jiska:
X^N == M -> return X
X^N < M  -> right side jao
X^N > M  -> left side jao

Steps:
1. Search space lo = 1 to M
2. mid nikalo
3. mid^N calculate karo
4. Agar mid^N == M -> mid answer
5. Agar mid^N < M -> low = mid + 1
6. Agar mid^N > M -> high = mid - 1
7. Agar loop khatam ho gaya aur exact match nahi mila -> return -1

Important:
mid^N calculate karte time overflow ho sakta hai,
isliye multiplication step by step karo aur beech mein check karo.

Time Complexity: O(log M * N)
Space Complexity: O(1)

One line intuition:
Binary search se aisa number find karo jiska power N exactly M ke equal ho.

#Code:

class Solution {

    public int NthRoot(int N, int M) {
        int low = 1;
        int high = M;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
            long val = power(mid, N, M);

            if(val == M){
                return mid;
            }
            else if(val < M){
                low = mid + 1;
            }
            else{
                high = mid - 1;
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }

    private long power(int base, int exp, int limit){
        long result = 1;
        for(int i = 0; i < exp; i++){
            result = result * base;
            if(result > limit){
                return result;
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}
